947.01(1) - Disorderly Conduct 
940.203(2) - Battery or Threat to Judge, Prosecutor, or Law Enforcement Officer

Shall maintain absolute sobriety - no alcohol or illegal drugs. 
Shall not possess any alcohol on person, in residence or occupied motor vehicle. 
No Taverns meaning the defendant shall not enter into or loiter near any establishment where the main purpose is the sale and/or consumption of alcohol, including liquor stores. 
Shall not have contact with Officer Buteyn, unless officer is on duty and it is an emergency.  No contact with residence or family members. No contact means no contact in person, in writing, by phone, computer, through a third person or otherwise, except through the defendant's attorney. 
Shall not have contact with any Walmart stores in Wisconsin. 
The defendant must have installed a Transdermal Alcohol Monitoring system before release.  Shall comply with all rules established by the vendor.
Shall not remove or otherwise tamper with the Transdermal Alcohol Monitoring system without court approval.  The Transdermal Alcohol Monitoring system may only be removed by the vendor. 
Shall not leave state of Wisconsin without permission of the Court. 
Shall not apply for a passport while case is pending.
